title: Matchsafe, "Woman's Leg", late 19th century
provenance: Collection of Carol B. Brener and Stephen W. Brener
creditline: Gift of Stephen W. Brener and Carol B. Brener
description: In the form of a woman's leg, from mid thigh down to the foot, knee slightly bent. Circular lid with thumb catch attached at thigh end of box, hinged on underside. Striker on top of lid.
